# 23. Delivery Phases

## Phase 1: Repository Foundation

Repositories:

```text
/Users/riowiraldhani/Documents/GitHub/remediation-core

/Users/riowiraldhani/Documents/GitHub/security-workflows
```

Deliverables:

* verify Git remotes;
* create initial folder structure;
* add README files;
* add contribution guidance;
* define initial licenses;
* add basic CI;
* define core-to-workflow compatibility.

## Phase 2: Remediation Core Prototype

Deliverables:

* Go CLI;
* job model;
* result model;
* Syft integration;
* Grype integration;
* finding normalization;
* npm direct-dependency adapter;
* minimum-safe resolver;
* update verification;
* result.json;
* unit and fixture tests.

No Pull Request creation.

## Phase 3: Core CLI Release

Deliverables:

* Dockerfile;
* GitHub Release workflow;
* Linux amd64 CLI binary;
* Linux arm64 CLI binary;
* release checksums;
* semantic version tag;
* pipeline usage documentation.

Example:

```text
https://github.com/opsbento/remediation-core/releases/download/v0.1.1/remediate-linux-amd64
```

Container distribution is deferred until the CLI release flow is stable.

## Phase 4: Centralized GitHub Workflow

Deliverables:

* reusable workflow;
* pinned remediation-core CLI release;
* caller workflow example;
* branch creation;
* commit creation;
* Pull Request creation;
* deduplication;
* artifact upload;
* GitHub job summary.

## Phase 5: End-to-End Testing

Test cases:

* vulnerable direct npm dependency with patch fix;
* vulnerable direct npm dependency with minor fix;
* major-only fix blocked;
* no known fix;
* transitive dependency skipped;
* unexpected file modification rejected;
* target finding remains after update;
* no finding;
* duplicate PR prevention.

## Phase 6: Additional Ecosystems

Order:

```text
Go Modules
Python Poetry or uv
Maven
Cargo
Gradle
```

## Phase 7: GitLab Integration

Reuse:

```text
remediation-core container
```

Add:

```text
GitLab CI template
GitLab Merge Request delivery adapter
```

