# 25. MVP Acceptance Criteria

The MVP is complete when:

1. both local repositories contain committed project structures;
2. remediation-core can run locally;
3. remediation-core does not require GitHub credentials;
4. a Node.js fixture contains a direct vulnerable dependency;
5. Syft identifies the dependency;
6. Grype identifies a High or Critical vulnerability;
7. the finding has a known fixed version;
8. the resolver confirms the target exists in the npm registry;
9. the resolver selects the minimum safe patch or minor version;
10. npm updates package.json;
11. npm updates package-lock.json;
12. lifecycle scripts are not executed;
13. only allowed files change;
14. Syft generates an updated SBOM;
15. Grype no longer detects the target vulnerability;
16. no new Critical vulnerability is introduced;
17. remediation-core produces result.json;
18. remediation-core is published as a pinned CLI release asset;
19. security-workflows invokes the pinned CLI release;
20. security-workflows creates a deterministic branch;
21. security-workflows creates a Pull Request;
22. rerunning the workflow does not create a duplicate Pull Request;
23. workflow artifacts contain before and after scan evidence;
24. application repositories only require a small caller workflow.

